{
  "texts": [
    "Our laboratory developed high-throughput tools to query echocardiogram videos and their metadata from Cedars-Sinai's internal databases at scale, view and classify videos and link them to associated structured reporting from cardiologists.",
    "DICOM images were queried from a Hyland vendor-neutral archive, linked to interpretations created by trained cardiologists using Syngo Dynamics and converted to AVI video files using PyDICOM before model training and inference.",
    "Data were split by patient into training, validation and internal test datasets.",
    "The training data contained 921,981 videos from 84,990 patients, the validation set contained 10,000 videos from 5,358 patients and the internal test set contained 100,994 videos from 10,001 patients.",
    "A random subset (n = 5,000) of the publicly released EchoNet-Dynamic dataset from Stanford Healthcare was used as an external test set."
  ]
}